# uv package manager

Use **uv** for this project. Do not use bare `python`, `pip`, or `pytest` when the intent is to run project tooling or install dependencies.

## Running commands

Prefix runnable tools with `uv run` so they use the project environment:

```bash
# ❌ BAD
pytest
python -m pytest
ruff check .

# ✅ GOOD
uv run pytest
uv run python -m pytest
uv run ruff check .
```

Use `uv run <tool>` for any CLI installed as a project dependency (pytest, ruff, mypy, black, etc.).

## Adding or updating packages

```bash
# ❌ BAD
pip install requests

# ✅ GOOD
uv add requests
```

For dev-only dependencies: `uv add --dev <package>`.

## Syncing the environment

When dependencies changed (e.g. after pulling `pyproject.toml` / `uv.lock`): `uv sync` (or `uv sync --dev` if the project uses dev groups).
